  "Title": "第1课 - Lunar Module Ingress",
  "Description": "欢迎来到登月舱学院。在这第一课中，我们将学习在建立对接后，如何从指挥舱进入登月舱。",
  "BriefingText": "简报\r\n\r\nInstructor: Patrick\r\nLevel: Advanced\r\nNote: All the Lunar Module lessons are considered advanced lessons, and require you to understand the mechanics of Reentry, and how to operate the Apollo Command Module.\r\n\r\nWelcome to the Lunar Module Academy, and the first lesson related to the Lunar Module.\r\n\r\nThe Lunar Module is a spacecraft designed to land two astronauts on the Moon. It will take the journey together with the Command and Service Module from launch to lunar orbit, where two astronauts will enter the Lunar Module, undock with the Command Module (operated by one astronaut alone), and perform the descent to the lunar surface, land, perform mission objectives, and then ascend back into lunar orbit to rendezvous and dock with the Command and Service Module again.\r\n\r\nIn this lesson, we will go through the steps needed to ingress into the Lunar Module from the Command Module. This involves pressurizing it, opening the hatch, and entering the Lunar Module.\r\nOnce the hatch is opened, all the flood lights in the Lunar Module will be illuminated so you can navigate inside it, and perform the setup.\r\n\r\nGood luck!",
